---
description: Do not use Default derive or #[default] on enums
alwaysApply: true
---
Do not derive `Default` on enums or use `#[default]` attributes on enum variants.

Enums represent explicit choices. Forcing callers to specify the variant makes code clearer and prevents accidental use of a default that may not be appropriate for the context.

```rust
// BAD
#[derive(Default)]
pub enum ButtonVariant {
    #[default]
    Primary,
    Secondary,
}

// GOOD
pub enum ButtonVariant {
    Primary,
    Secondary,
}
```

Similarly, avoid `#[props(default)]` on enum-typed component props in Dioxus.
